{"id": 114434, "acmi_id": "B2003274", "title": "[KenRa Films Present: the Kenneth Rankine Home Movie Collection: Reel 19]", "title_zh_hans": "", "title_pa": "", "title_hi": "", "title_annotation": "", "title_annotation_zh_hans": "", "title_annotation_pa": "", "title_annotation_hi": "", "slug": "kenra-films-present-the-kenneth-rankine-home-movie-collection-reel-19", "creator_credit": "Kenneth Rankine", "credit_line": "", "credit_line_zh_hans": "", "credit_line_pa": "", "credit_line_hi": "", "headline_credit": "Australia, 1944", "video_links": [{"id": 1096, "name": "ACMI External Digital Access Copy", "uri": "https://youtu.be/Km1-gJG0pdQ"}], "record_type": "work", "type": "Film", "is_on_display": false, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI Cafe Window Screens", "last_on_display_date": "2019-04-22", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "", "unpublished": false, "external": false, "first_production_date": "1944-01-01T11:00:00+11:00", "commissioned": false, "public_domain": false, "external_references": [], "brief_description": "<p>Kenneth Carruthers Rankine (1890 - 1968) was a keen amateur cinematographer and filmmaker. This collection of his home movies has been donated to ACMI by Kenneth&#8217;s granddaughter. The collection represents a wonderful slice of life in Australia; with contents including scenes of everyday life, major family occasions, holidays around Victoria and views of Melbourne.</p>\n<p>This film shows views across the Melbourne CBD rooftops and steeples, a selection of &#8216;flowering gums&#8217;, a visit to the Botanical Gardens, the arrival of &#8216;flat tops&#8217; aircraft carrier ships. Kenneth then shows off the neon signs of Melbourne at night.</p>\n<p>Selected highlights list:</p>\n<p>00:00:20:00 title &#8216;Melbourne&#8217;.</p>\n<p>00:00:26:00 views from what appears to be the top of the Royal Melbourne Children’s Hospital in North Melbourne with a note, &#8216;From Here 178 Feet&#8217; beginning with a view down Elizabeth St toward the CBD.</p>\n<p>00:01:06:00 an eastern view, where the Dandenong Ranges can be seen in the distance.</p>\n<p>00:01:28:00 to 00:01:37:00 views over Melbourne University toward Queen’s College and the Royal Exhibition Building.</p>\n<p>00:01:58:00 a horse and cart enter a city intersection at same time as a tram and cars.</p>\n<p>00:02:47:00 Melbourne Technical College rotunda.</p>\n<p>00:03:05:00 the Pelaco sign in Richmond (a Heritage Victoria listed landmark). Pelaco is a Melbourne based shirt manufacturing business.</p>\n<p>00:30:00:00 Elizabeth St with Flinders St Station in view ends the footage of the rooftops of Melbourne.</p>\n<p>00:04:30:00 title card &#8216;Flowering Gums&#8217; followed by a selection of trees and shrubs in flower.</p>\n<p>00:06:52:00 title card &#8216;Botanical Gardens&#8217; begins a look at people enjoying the gardens. Footage includes examples of fox furs being worn by some women strolling in the gardens.</p>\n<p>00:09:28:00 a quick look at what appears to be Captain Cook&#8217;s cottage.</p>\n<p>00:09:35:00 title card &#8216;V.A.C.S On Location&#8217; begins a sequence of what appears to be a film being made.</p>\n<p>00:10:45:00 title card &#8216;The Flat Tops Arrive&#8217; footage of large ships (aircraft carriers) and tugboats in the bay viewed by watchers on a small pier near, presumably, Port Melbourne.</p>\n<p>00:12:42:00 a plane goes overhead. The sequence ends at at night on the beach. with people overlooking the bay toward the horizon.</p>\n<p>00:15:11:00 title &#8216;Bright Lights&#8217;, a sequence at night showing neon signs around Melbourne.</p>\n<p>00:16:03:00 the face of Luna Park in St Kilda.</p>\n<p>00:16:24:00 Fostor&#8217;s Lager advertising sign.</p>\n<p>00:16:35:00 Berger Paints (British Paints) advertising sign.</p>\n<p>00:16:40:00 to 00:16:55:00 Swallows and Ariells &#8216;Follow the Swallow&#8217; sequenced advertisement for Uneeda Biscuits, Plum Pudding and Biscuits Cakes Ice cream.</p>\n<p>00:16:58:00 Sunshine Milk advertising sign.</p>\n<p>00:17:15:00 Ball and Welch department store sign on Flinders St with the T&amp;G Building sign in the background.</p>\n<p>00:17:23:00 shows a longer sequence advertisement for Sennets ice cream featuring a bear eating an ice cream.</p>\n<p>00:18:00:00 possibly the top dome of the Royal Exhibition Building lit up.</p>\n<p>00:18:25:00 &#8216;Visit the Zoo&#8217; advertising flashes up on screen.</p>\n<p>00:19:05:00 advertisement &#8216;Mascot Underwear for Men and Boys&#8217; featuring a ram and lamb on his back.</p>\n<p>00:19:09:00 &#8216;Dunlop Tyres&#8217; advertising sign.</p>\n<p>00:19:33:00 footage ends with blurred city lights and traffic lights turning to red.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>Kenneth Rankine</p>", "creator_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "creator_credit_for_label_pa": "", "creator_credit_for_label_hi": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>Australia, 1944</p>", "headline_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "headline_credit_for_label_pa": "", "headline_credit_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_pa": "", "title_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_override_pa": "", "title_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_for_label_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_pa": "", "description_for_label_hi": "", "description_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_override_pa": "", "description_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": "", "title_for_label": "<p>[KenRa Films Present: the Kenneth Rankine Home Movie Collection: Reel 19]</p>", "description": "<p>Kenneth Carruthers Rankine (1890 - 1968) was a keen amateur cinematographer and filmmaker. This collection of his home movies has been donated to ACMI b